\label{lem:adjoinCommRingOfComm_mathlib}
\lean{Algebra.adjoinCommRingOfComm}
\mathlibok
\textit{Provided by Mathlib
(\texttt{Mathlib.Algebra.Algebra.Subalgebra.Lattice}).}
Let \(R\) be a commutative ring and \(A\) an \(R\)-algebra, possibly
noncommutative. If \(s \subseteq A\) is a set of pairwise-commuting elements
(\(a b = b a\) for all \(a, b \in s\)), then the \(R\)-subalgebra
\(\mathrm{adjoin}_R(s)\) generated by \(s\) carries a \(\mathrm{CommRing}\)
structure. Applied to the \(r\) pairwise-commuting degree-raising endomorphisms

